<title type="html"><![CDATA[One of the many legendary men of a land once known for being a center of Hadith—Al-Andalus]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="https://forum.salafiri.com/viewtopic.php?t=397&amp;p=426#p426"><![CDATA[
<blockquote class="uncited"><div><br />ولم يكن (أي: بقي بن مخلد، رحمه الله) بالمالكي، ولا الحنبلي، ولا الظاهري الصرف، ولكنه قال بترك التمذهب، والعمل بالنصوص<br /><br />And he (Baqi Bin Makhlad, rahimahu Allah) was neither a Maliki, nor a Hanbali, nor was he a pure Dhahiri; however he called for the abandoning of Madhhabism, and called towards acting on the Texts.<br /></div></blockquote><br />—Dr. Ahmad Bukair Mahmud, hafithahu Allah, or rahimahu Allah in any case, Al-Madrasat Al-Dhahiriyyah Bil Mashriq Wal-Maghrib, p. 32, publ. Dar Qutaibah<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://forum.salafiri.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=110">مذهب العمل بالحديث</a> — Sat Sep 17, 2016 12:24 am</p><hr />
